</span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2532622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 24, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ucb1665702704561.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ucb1665702704561.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ucb1665702704561.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ucb1665702704561\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Locking Support on Microsoft SQL Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__section_w3426ab1b5b1_w3427ab1b5_w3428ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__section_yn2_z4l_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1131144e59\">Locking</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Locking Support</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__1\">Locking </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__1\">Optimistic </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__2\">MSS optimistic locking is used. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__1\">Cautious </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__2\">MSS update locks are issued when a user starts\n                        an update (default). </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__1\">Paranoid </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ucb1665702704561__table_d4916e1_d4917e1_d4918e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">MSS update locks are issued when a user starts an update with the\n                              <code class=\"ph codeph\">read/lock</code> statement.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__p_d53024e1_d53025e1_d53026e1\">If a deadlock occurs, the MSS connector raises an\n            error in its internal error handling mechanism. When a logon path is marked as\n            deadlocked, no work is allowed on that path until the path transaction is ended.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__section_hcj_bpl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1131144e129\">read/lock </h2>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__note_ifh_dpl_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Using the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">/lock</code> statement immediately forces a holdlock\n            in MS-SQL, that prevents all other users from writing to the record concerned (or to any\n            other record in the locked page); this does not prevent users from reading these\n            records, however.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__p_d53030e1_d53031e1_d53032e1\">If another user tries to write to a record that has a\n            holdlock applied to it, the operation fails and the following occurs:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__ul_kfh_dpl_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__li_d24872e1_d24873e1_d24874e1\">Microsoft SQL Server waits for the blocking lock\n               to be released with a time-out specified by the lock timeout assignment setting. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__li_d24875e1_d24876e1_d24877e1\">If the lock is not released, a deadlock develops\n               and the transaction fails for the user having the least CPU time in their\n               transaction. </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__p_d53033e1_d53034e1_d53035e1\">Normally, Uniface sets <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> to\n            -10 if a user tries to modify and store a record which has been locked by another user,\n            but because Microsoft SQL Server does not return a status in this situation, Uniface is\n            unable to do this.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__section_gyp_dpl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1131144e161\">Lock Granularity</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__p_d53039e1_d53040e1_d53041e1\">Under normal circumstances, the unit of locking is\n            left to the DBMS. It is possible to explicitly specify the following locking units:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__ul_cbl_fpl_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__li_d24878e1_d24879e1_d24880e1\">Page lock </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__li_d24881e1_d24882e1_d24883e1\">Row locks </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__li_d24884e1_d24885e1_d24886e1\">Table locks </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__section_wps_fpl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1131144e182\">Lock Isolation</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ucb1665702704561__p_d53045e1_d53046e1_d53047e1\">You can set the isolation of a transaction using the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lock isolation</span> connector option. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zmh1665702705308.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zmh1665702705308.html\" title=\"Set the isolation level for the database transactions of the connector.\">lock isolation</a>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532622\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Locking Support on Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 24, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Locking Support on Microsoft SQL Server Locking Table 1. Locking Support Locking Description Optimistic MSS optimistic locking is used. Cautious MSS update locks are issued when a user starts an update (default). Paranoid MSS update locks are issued when a user starts an update with the read/lock statement. If a deadlock occurs, the MSS connector raises an error in its internal error handling mechanism. When a logon path is marked as deadlocked, no work is allowed on that path until the path transaction is ended. read/lock CAUTION: Using the read /lock statement immediately forces a holdlock in MS-SQL, that prevents all other users from writing to the record concerned (or to any other record in the locked page); this does not prevent users from reading these records, however. If another user tries to write to a record that has a holdlock applied to it, the operation fails and the following occurs: Microsoft SQL Server waits for the blocking lock to be released with a time-out specified by the lock timeout assignment setting. If the lock is not released, a deadlock develops and the transaction fails for the user having the least CPU time in their transaction. Normally, Uniface sets $status to -10 if a user tries to modify and store a record which has been locked by another user, but because Microsoft SQL Server does not return a status in this situation, Uniface is unable to do this. Lock Granularity Under normal circumstances, the unit of locking is left to the DBMS. It is possible to explicitly specify the following locking units: Page lock Row locks Table locks Lock Isolation You can set the isolation of a transaction using the lock isolation connector option. For more information, see lock isolation . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}